videos.description: Michael Buffer introduces Kentucky starting lineup against Kansas.
videos.headline: Michael Buffer gets Rupp Arena ready for Kansas-Kentucky

videos.description: Dominique Hawkins gets the rebound, feeds the pass to Monk for the layup.
videos.headline: Malik Monk goes high for the layup

videos.description: Devonte' Graham feeds Lagerald Vick for a two-handed slam late in the first half.
videos.headline: Kansas' Vick throws down two-handed slam

videos.description: Kentucky head coach John Calipari discussing his team's first half performance.
videos.headline: Kentucky head coach John Calipari discussing his team's first half performance

videos.description: Malik Monk with the nifty behind-the-back feed sets up Edrice Adebayo for the dunk.
videos.headline: Monk's behind-the-back pass sets up Adebayo's dunk

videos.description: With Kentucky in transition, De'Aaron Fox misses the layup, but Dominique Hawkins is there to tip in the shot.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Hawkins tips the ball in for the basket

videos.description: Josh Jackson describes how Kansas' defense and confidence were huge factors in the 79-73 win over Kentucky.
videos.headline: Jackson says confidence was key in Kansas' win

videos.description: Frank Mason III leads No. 2 Kansas with 21 points while Josh Jackson records 20 points and 10 rebounds in a 79-73 win over No. 4 Kentucky.
videos.headline: Mason, Jackson lead Kansas past Kentucky
